HEADWORD: Baggage master
<hw>Bag"gage mas`ter</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <def>One who has charge of the
baggage at a railway station or upon a line of public travel.</def>
<mark>[U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

